edu.cnm.deepdive.project_titan.service

Interface BaseFluentAsyncTask.Transformer<Intermediate,Result>

  • Type Parameters:
    Intermediate - type of result data produced by the basic background processing of the asynchronous task (returned by BaseFluentAsyncTask.perform(Object[]) and consumed by transform(Object), or (usually) Void if the background processing is not intended to return a result.
    Result - type of result produced by the transform processing of the asynchronous task (returned by transform(Object) and consumed by BaseFluentAsyncTask.onPostExecute(Object) and BaseFluentAsyncTask.onCancelled(Object), or (usually) Void if the background processing is not intended to return a result.
    Enclosing class:
    BaseFluentAsyncTask<Params,Progress,Intermediate,Result>

    public static interface BaseFluentAsyncTask.Transformer<Intermediate,Result>
    Declares a transform(Object) method that can be implemented to perform additional background processing following successful completion of the BaseFluentAsyncTask.perform(Object[]) method.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Result transform(Intermediate intermediate)
      Transforms the intermediate data to a final result.

    • Method Detail

      • transform

        Result transform(Intermediate intermediate)
          throws BaseFluentAsyncTask.TaskException
        Transforms the intermediate data to a final result. (These may be of different types, depending on the instance declaration or subclass definition.)
        Parameters:
        intermediate - intermediate results, returned by BaseFluentAsyncTask.perform(Object[]).
        Returns:
        final results, passed to BaseFluentAsyncTask.onPostExecute(Object) or BaseFluentAsyncTask.onCancelled(Object).
        Throws:
        BaseFluentAsyncTask.TaskException - to indicate unsuccessful completion.
